OL,3,CGovernment lines up insolvency firm in
OL,4,Ccase of Thames Water collapse
OL,6,FThe Government has appointed
OL,7,Finsolvency specialists to step up
OL,8,Fplanning for Thames Water in case the
OL,9,Ftroubled water company collapses.
OL,11,FEnvironment Secretary Steve Reed
OL,12,Fsigned off the appointment, with Sky
OL,13,FNews reporting FTI Consulting will act
OL,14,Fas an administrator in case Thames
OL,15,Ffails to secure funding from lenders.
OL,17,FContingency plans could see Britain's
OL,18,Fbiggest water firm placed into a
OL,19,Fspecial administration regime (SAR),
OL,20,Fmeaning it would be put into an
OL,21,Finsolvency process.
